This \u0002sVU21H6GAqBwAU8Z\u0002 allows to tune (\u0002sVU21H6GAqBwAU8Z$hQmNW36GAqBwAUFq\u0002 and \u0002sVU21H6GAqBwAU8Z$slWQp36GAqBwAacy\u0002) the volume of the input signal processed by \u0002_onW1H6GAqBwAU75$EhrM236GAqBwAUY0\u0002.

The pin \u0002sVU21H6GAqBwAU8Z$116VW36GAqBwAUFT\u0002 must be connected to \u0002P_dPq36GAqBwAWSe$Qvkca36GAqBwAYL7\u0002 pin of \u0002P_dPq36GAqBwAWSe\u0002.

The pin \u0002sVU21H6GAqBwAU8Z$w4mVW36GAqBwAUFX\u0002 must be connected to \u0002P_dPq36GAqBwAWSe$EtCca36GAqBwAYL9\u0002. Due to the connection to \u0002P_dPq36GAqBwAWSe$Qvkca36GAqBwAYL7\u0002 the voltage at this pin can be tuned in the voltage range between 6.6mV (minimum volume) and 3.3V (maximum volume).

Finally, the pin \u0002sVU21H6GAqBwAU8Z$yhGVW36GAqBwAUFV\u0002 will be connected to ground reference provided by \u0002_onW1H6GAqBwAU75$dkFn.36GAqBwAU56\u0002.
AssociationEnd.Documentation_plain: This 10K_t20%_LOG_POT_H20mm_THT allows to tune (tuneR() and tuneL()) the volume of the input signal processed by uP : uP_SignalMusicProcessing. The pin VDD() must be connected to OUT_3V3A() pin of DAISY_SEED. The pin F_T() must be connected to ADC_IN1(). Due to the connection to OUT_3V3A() the voltage at this pin can be tuned in the voltage range between 6.6mV (minimum volume) and 3.3V (maximum volume). Finally, the pin GND() will be connected to ground reference provided by CONN1 : 5mm7_2mm_DC_THT.
AssociationEnd.Name: POT1

  • Volume percentage
  • Current effect parameter value

In order to avoid digital noise on \u0002P_dPq36GAqBwAWSe$Qvkca36GAqBwAYL7\u0002 pin of \u0002P_dPq36GAqBwAWSe\u0002, the \u0002_onW1H6GAqBwAU75$UqMB.36GAqBwAUnW\u0002 is supplied directly by the DC voltage brought to \u0002GQQO1H6GAqBwAU9I\u0002 connector. AssociationEnd.Documentation_plain: The OLED : OLED_module is used to show: Current effect Volume percentage Current effect parameter value In order to avoid digital noise on OUT_3V3A() pin of DAISY_SEED, the OLED : OLED_module is supplied directly by the DC voltage brought to 5mm7_2mm_DC_THT connector. \u000221sVxb6GAqBwASC0\u0002 pushes and releases the next effect button (the button close to the right arrow). A signal is sent to \u0002_onW1H6GAqBwAU75\u0002 in order to change to the next processing effect between the ones available, according to the effect sequence delay -> tremolo -> phaser -> delay, and so on.

The delay effect allows to apply a temporal delay to the input audio signal. Then the delayed signal is overlapped to the original one in order to have an effect that is similar to the echo.

The tremolo effect applies a little amplitude modulation to the input audio signal.

The phaser effect applies a phase shift to the input audio signal.

The new effect name is displayed on the \u00022rATaP6GAqBwAXk6\u0002.

Components accessible from the outside must be Through-Hole devices (THT) because they provide a better mechanical attach to the board. Instead, for all the other components Surface Mount Technology (SMT) can be more useful in case of high speed signals. The PCB must have 4 holes to be fixed to the case. Hole diameter must be 5mm. the holes centers coordinates in mm (origin in the bottom left corner of the PCB): - 5,5 - 100.5, 5 - 64, 5 - 100.5, 64.5 No components in the next 5mm around these holes. A couple of BoardToBoard_20_2mm54_SMD useful to connect the DAISY_SEED must be placed in the middle of PCB, parallel to the shortest side of the board. Then components that allows User to provide input must be placed on the left side. The OLED_module, instead, must be placed on the right. As far as connectors, they must be placed in order to have the entry oriented towards the outside: - 5mm7_2mm_DC_THT for the Power_supply and cable, on the left, having the entry exposed on the shorter side of the board - 6mm35_JACK_Female_THT for the Jack_IN, on the right, having the entry exposed on the longest side of the board (left, looking at the board top layer) - 6mm35_JACK_Female_THT for the Jack_OUT, on the right, having the entry exposed on the longest side of the board (right, looking at the board top layer)
Specifications: - Width: 69mm - Length: 105.5mm - Core material: FR-4 - Board thickness: 1.6mm - Material TG: 145-150C - Copper thickness: 0.035mm

The switch is an ON-OFF switch. There is a lever that can be in two different positions. When position of lever is modified, it remains in that position until lever is moved again in the opposite one.

So it can be in two states:

  • ON: circuit is connected to voltage supply
  • OFF: circuit is not supplied

The switch remains in a state until the lever is moved in the opposite position.

This switch is a SPDT (Single Pole Double Throw) with a common pin (\u0002ZK321H6GAqBwAU8x$RE7mW36GAqBwATcz\u0002) that can be shorted to \u0002ZK321H6GAqBwAU8x$ooCmW36GAqBwATcx\u0002 or \u0002ZK321H6GAqBwAU8x$yJ7mW36GAqBwATc1\u0002.

Body must be higher than approximately 20mm.

In the following image is reported an example of toggle switch.

Electrical characteristics:

  • Insulation resistance: more than 1000MOhm
  • Contact resistance: less than 20mOhm
  • Maximum current: 5A

Mechanical characteristics:

  • Through-hole technology
  • 50000 cycles
  • Total height (without considering lever): at least 2cm
  • Circular diameter: 5.72mm

- Contact resistance: less than 20mOhm

- 50000 cycles

- Circular diameter: 5.72mm

The switch is an ON-OFF switch. There is a lever that can be in two different positions. When position of lever is modified, it remains in that position until lever is moved in the opposite one.

So it can be in two states:

- ON: circuit is connected to voltage supply

- OFF: circuit is not supplied

The switch remains in a state until the lever is moved in the opposite position.

This switch is a SPDT (Single Pole Double Throw) with a common pin (\u0002ZK321H6GAqBwAU8x$RE7mW36GAqBwATcz\u0002) that can be shorted to \u0002ZK321H6GAqBwAU8x$ooCmW36GAqBwATcx\u0002 or \u0002ZK321H6GAqBwAU8x$yJ7mW36GAqBwATc1\u0002.

Body must be higher approximately 20mm in order to guarantee that the lever is outside the \u00020jtJ1H6GAqBwAVFk\u0002.

In the following image is reported an example of toggle switch.

Electrical characteristics:

- Insulation resistance: more than 1000MOhm

- Contact resistance: less than 20mOhm

- Maximum current: 5A

Mechanical characteristics:

- Through-hole technology

- 50000 cycles

- Total height (without considering lever): at least 2cm

- Circular diameter: 5.72mm

Delay effect stores a copy of the input signal and applies a temporal delay to it. Then, the delayed signal is added to the input signal and this process can be replicated with a lowering amplitude of the reproduced replica.

The user-tunable parameter is Time delay, which sets the delay between the original signal and the copies.

This function takes in input one float sample and processes it according to the delay effect.

Operation.Documentation:
Phaser effect applies a phase shift to the input signal controlled by a Low Frequency Oscillator and then adds back the processed signal inverted by 180° with the original input signal.

The effect of this processing for the listener is a slow modulation of the signal.

There are two user-tunable parameters Frequency, which sets the frequency of the LFO.

This function takes in input one float sample and processes it according to the phaser effect.
